---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro'
import { createWebPageSchema } from '~/utils/schema'

export const prerender = true

const pageSchema = createWebPageSchema({
  name: 'Grand Shambala – The world\'s largest load-bearing straw building',
  url: Astro.url.toString(),
  description:
    'How a small group built the world\'s largest load-bearing straw building: 850 m², two storeys, 75 days. From Earthship intuition to lime renders, the full story of an extraordinary build in an eco-place in the south of Aveyron.',
})
---

<Layout
  title="Grand Shambala – The world's largest load-bearing straw building | LAOM"
  description="How a small group built the world's largest load-bearing straw building: 850 m², two storeys, 75 days. Full story of the build at LAOM."
  seo={{ ldJSON: pageSchema }}
>

  <!-- Playfair Display for article headings -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,500&display=swap" />

  <style is:inline>
    .font-playfair { font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; }
    @media (min-width: 1400px) { #sticky-toc { display: block !important; } }
    section[id] { scroll-margin-top: 6rem; }
  </style>

  <!-- Progress bar -->
  <div id="progress-bar" role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="0" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="position: fixed; bottom: 0; left: 0; height: 6px; background-color: #C4A855; z-index: 9999; width: 0%; box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(196, 168, 85, 0.4); transition: none; pointer-events: none;"></div>

  <!-- Sticky sidebar TOC,  minimal dots-only design -->
  <nav id="sticky-toc" aria-label="Article table of contents" style="position: fixed; top: 140px; right: 32px; z-index: 50; opacity: 0; pointer-events: none; transition: opacity 0.3s ease; display: none;">
    <div class="flex flex-col items-end gap-[2px]">
      <a href="#lhomme" data-toc="lhomme" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 1,  Where it all began">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">Where it all began</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#la-graine" data-toc="la-graine" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 2,  The Seed">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">The Seed</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#les-murs-qui-parlent" data-toc="les-murs-qui-parlent" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 3,  The Straw Walls">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">The Straw Walls</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#le-mur" data-toc="le-mur" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 4,  The Wall">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">The Wall</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#lautomne" data-toc="lautomne" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 5,  Vertical Autumn">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">Vertical Autumn</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#le-silence" data-toc="le-silence" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 6,  The Year of Silence">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">The Silence</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#la-peau" data-toc="la-peau" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 7,  The Skin">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">The Skin</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#programme" data-toc="programme" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 8,  What the building contains">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">The Programme</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#lhorizon" data-toc="lhorizon" class="toc-link group flex items-center gap-3 py-[6px] transition-all duration-300" aria-label="Chapter 9,  The Horizon">
        <span class="toc-label text-xs font-light text-[#2C2824]/0 group-hover:text-[#2C2824]/50 transition-all duration-300 whitespace-nowrap translate-x-2 group-hover:translate-x-0">The Horizon</span>
        <span class="toc-dot w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-[#2C2824]/15 transition-all duration-300 shrink-0"></span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
      var bar = document.getElementById('progress-bar');
      if (bar) {
        var ticking = false;
        function updateProgress() {
          var scrollTop = window.scrollY || document.documentElement.scrollTop;
          var docHeight = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
          var progress = docHeight > 0 ? Math.min((scrollTop / docHeight) * 100, 100) : 0;
          bar.style.width = progress + '%';
          bar.setAttribute('aria-valuenow', Math.round(progress));
          ticking = false;
        }
        window.addEventListener('scroll', function () {
          if (!ticking) { requestAnimationFrame(updateProgress); ticking = true; }
        }, { passive: true });
        updateProgress();
      }
      var stickyToc = document.getElementById('sticky-toc');
      var inlineToc = document.getElementById('inline-toc');
      var ctaSection = document.getElementById('cta-section');
      if (stickyToc && inlineToc) {
        var tocVisible = false;
        var ctaReached = false;
        var inlineTocObserver = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
          tocVisible = !entries[0].isIntersecting && entries[0].boundingClientRect.bottom < 0;
          stickyToc.style.opacity = (tocVisible && !ctaReached) ? '1' : '0';
          stickyToc.style.pointerEvents = (tocVisible && !ctaReached) ? 'auto' : 'none';
        }, { threshold: 0 });
        inlineTocObserver.observe(inlineToc);
        if (ctaSection) {
          var ctaObserver = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
            ctaReached = entries[0].isIntersecting;
            stickyToc.style.opacity = (tocVisible && !ctaReached) ? '1' : '0';
            stickyToc.style.pointerEvents = (tocVisible && !ctaReached) ? 'auto' : 'none';
          }, { threshold: 0 });
          ctaObserver.observe(ctaSection);
        }
      }
      var sections = document.querySelectorAll('section[id]');
      var tocLinks = document.querySelectorAll('#sticky-toc .toc-link');
      var currentActive = null;
      if (sections.length && tocLinks.length) {
        var chapterObserver = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
          entries.forEach(function (entry) {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              var activeId = entry.target.id;
              if (currentActive === activeId) return;
              currentActive = activeId;
              tocLinks.forEach(function (link) {
                var id = link.getAttribute('data-toc');
                var dot = link.querySelector('.toc-dot');
                var isActive = id === activeId;
                var label = link.querySelector('.toc-label');
                link.setAttribute('aria-current', isActive ? 'true' : 'false');
                if (dot) {
                  dot.style.backgroundColor = isActive ? '#C4A855' : '';
                  dot.style.width = isActive ? '8px' : '';
                  dot.style.height = isActive ? '8px' : '';
                  dot.style.boxShadow = isActive ? '0 0 6px rgba(196,168,85,0.4)' : '';
                }
                if (label) {
                  label.style.color = isActive ? 'rgba(44,40,36,0.7)' : '';
                  label.style.fontWeight = isActive ? '500' : '';
                }
              });
            }
          });
        }, { rootMargin: '-15% 0px -65% 0px' });
        sections.forEach(function (s) { chapterObserver.observe(s); });
      }
    });
  </script>


  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative w-full -mt-24 md:-mt-28">
    <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/grand-shambala-vue-drone-paille-porteuse-aveyron.webp" alt="Drone view of Grand Shambala, 850 m² of load-bearing straw in the Aveyron landscape" title="Grand Shambala seen from above, Aveyron" class="w-full min-h-[60vh] md:min-h-0 object-cover object-center" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/20 to-transparent flex flex-col items-center justify-end pb-12 md:pb-20 gap-3 md:gap-4">
      <h1 class="font-playfair text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-medium text-white tracking-tight drop-shadow-lg text-center px-6">
        Grand Shambala
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm md:text-base font-light tracking-[0.08em] text-white/80 max-w-lg text-center px-6 drop-shadow-md">
        The world's largest load-bearing straw building, 850&nbsp;m² on two storeys
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- INTRO -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-[#FAF8F5]">
    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">

      <p class="text-xs font-medium tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mb-8">Introduction</p>

      <p class="font-playfair text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed text-[#2C2824] mb-6">
        Grand Shambala is the heart of LAOM, an eco-place nestled in 21 hectares of wild nature in the south of Aveyron.
      </p>
      <p class="font-playfair text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed text-[#2C2824] mb-6">
        850&nbsp;m² on two storeys: coliving, housing, workshops, common space, entirely built in load-bearing straw, wood, earth and lime. A passive building, close to autonomy, where you only breathe natural materials.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        This page tells how it was built: the steps, the choices, the difficulties, and how they were overcome. You'll read how four people raised the walls in fifteen days, how a steel structure was abandoned because it contradicted our values, and how three insulation blowing machines failed before the right one was found.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- TABLE OF CONTENTS -->
  <section id="inline-toc" class="py-14 lg:py-16 bg-white border-t border-black/5">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-playfair text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-[#2C2824] tracking-tight">Table of contents</h2>
        <p class="text-sm font-light text-[#2C2824]/50">~18 min read</p>
      </div>
      <nav aria-label="Table of contents" class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-2">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mb-3">Act I,  The Vision</p>
          <a href="#lhomme" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">1. Where it all began</a>
          <a href="#la-graine" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">2. The Seed</a>
          <a href="#les-murs-qui-parlent" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">3. The Straw Walls</a>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mt-6 mb-3">Act II,  The Wall</p>
          <a href="#le-mur" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">4. The Wall</a>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mt-6 mb-3">Act III,  The Build</p>
          <a href="#lautomne" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">5. Vertical Autumn</a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mb-3">Act IV,  The Silence</p>
          <a href="#le-silence" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">6. The Year of Silence</a>
          <a href="#la-peau" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">7. The Skin</a>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mt-6 mb-3">Act V,  The Horizon</p>
          <a href="#programme" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">8. What the building contains</a>
          <a href="#lhorizon" class="block text-lg font-light text-[#2C2824]/75 hover:text-[#2C2824] transition-colors py-1.5">9. The Horizon</a>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- CHAPTER 1,  WHERE IT ALL BEGAN -->

  <section id="lhomme" class="py-24 lg:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">
      <span class="block text-xs font-light tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mb-6">Chapter 1</span>
      <h2 class="font-playfair text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-medium text-[#2C2824] mb-12 tracking-tight leading-tight">
        Where it all began
      </h2>

      <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/charly-aubert-portrait-debut-projet-grand-shambala.webp" alt="Portrait of Charly, early days of the Grand Shambala project" title="Charly Aubert, founder of LAOM" class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover rounded-sm mb-10" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        <span class="text-5xl font-light text-[#2C2824] float-left mr-3 mt-1 leading-none font-playfair">G</span>rand Shambala began in a field. A gently sloping plot in the south of Aveyron, in the heart of the Grands Causses Natural Park. We looked at that meadow and saw a building. Not a plan, not a concept—a building. 850 m² of floor space, two storeys, straw, wood, earth.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We had no money. No construction experience. Not even the land yet. But we had clarity about what needed to be done. And the first question was never « is it possible? ». The first question was: what do we need to do? What's the first step?
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed">
        This is the story of that building.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- CHAPTER 2,  THE SEED -->

  <section id="la-graine" class="py-24 lg:py-32 bg-[#FAF8F5]">
    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">
      <span class="block text-xs font-light tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mb-6">Chapter 2</span>
      <h2 class="font-playfair text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-medium text-[#2C2824] mb-12 tracking-tight leading-tight">
        The Seed
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The starting inspiration was Earthships—those buildings invented by American architect Michael Reynolds in the New Mexico desert. An Earthship is a self-sufficient building: it heats itself, collects its own water, recycles its waste, and feeds its inhabitants from an integrated greenhouse. A living organism.
      </p>

      <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/diagramme-6-principes-earthship-solaire-thermique.webp" alt="Diagram of the 6 Earthship principles: passive solar, thermal mass, water management, recycling, food production, energy autonomy" title="The 6 founding principles of the Earthship concept" class="w-full rounded-sm my-12" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        But an Earthship is designed for an isolated family. We were eleven, in a 21-hectare eco-place with a river, meadows, forests, and a collective project combining housing, outward-facing economic activity, and farming. A single classic Earthship building wasn't possible. We had to think systemically.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        And it wasn't just the Earthship. There was also the philosophy of the regenerative movement: how to shift from an extractive logic—taking more than we give—to a regenerative one, where every action enriches the system. How to integrate these variables into the design of a building?
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The Earthship's integrated greenhouse? We didn't need it in the building—we had the option of a real market garden at the scale of the estate, Ferme du Verseau, in regenerative agriculture. Passive solar gain? We kept it with a large south-facing glazed façade. Water autonomy? It's designed around the river and springs. Each principle found its place not in a single building, but in an entire ecosystem.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="my-12 py-8 border-l-2 border-[#C4A855] pl-8">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light italic text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed">
          What if, instead of shrinking the dream to fit the technique, we expanded the technique to welcome the dream?
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24 mt-12">
      <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/comparaison-earthship-vs-grand-shambala-collectif.webp" alt="Classic Earthship vs Grand Shambala, from individual module to collective ecosystem" title="From individual module to collective village" class="w-full rounded-sm" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      <p class="text-center text-sm font-light italic text-[#2C2824]/40 mt-4">From module to world</p>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24 mt-12">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/croquis-v1-premieres-esquisses-grand-shambala.webp" alt="Sketch v1, first drafts of Grand Shambala" title="Initial design sketch" class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover rounded-sm" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/croquis-v2-iteration-structure-grand-shambala.webp" alt="Sketch v2, structure iteration" title="Second iteration of the structure" class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover rounded-sm" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/croquis-v3-plan-rejete-grand-shambala.webp" alt="Sketch v3, rejected plan" title="Plan discarded during design" class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover rounded-sm" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/croquis-v4-plan-final-paille-porteuse.webp" alt="Sketch v4, final load-bearing straw plan" title="Final plan chosen for construction" class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover rounded-sm" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      </div>
      <p class="text-center text-sm font-light italic text-[#2C2824]/40 mt-4">The evolution of the thinking: sketches, iterations, rejected plans.</p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- CHAPTER 3,  THE STRAW WALLS -->

  <section id="les-murs-qui-parlent" class="py-24 lg:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">
      <span class="block text-xs font-light tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mb-6">Chapter 3</span>
      <h2 class="font-playfair text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-medium text-[#2C2824] mb-12 tracking-tight leading-tight">
        The Straw Walls
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The first version of Grand Shambala was a steel structure. A metal skeleton clad in a coat of straw. On paper it worked. Structurally it was solid. We even had access to steel.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        And then we stopped. Because an ecological building held up by steel is a contradiction. Steel is one of the most carbon-intensive materials there is. And to support it we needed large concrete pads, heavy foundations, an amount of concrete that contradicted everything we stood for.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="my-12 py-8 border-l-2 border-[#C4A855] pl-8">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light italic text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed">
          The steel worked. But an ecological building held up by carbon is a structural lie.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We pivoted to something more radical and more coherent: <strong>pure load-bearing straw</strong>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The principle: straw bales are not infill. They <em>are</em> the structure. They carry the walls, the roof, the floor. 850 m² on two storeys, held up by straw. It had never been done at this scale.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The advantage: very little concrete. Only foundation footings. No concrete slab, just frost protection. The rest: straw, local wood, earth, lime. Materials that store carbon instead of emitting it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed">
        North and west faces: load-bearing straw. South face: timber frame, to accommodate the large glazed façade that captures the sun. A bioclimatic building, structurally honest.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24 mt-12">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
        <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/coupe-technique-mur-paille-porteuse-detail.webp" alt="Technical section of load-bearing straw wall, detail view" title="Close-up of the straw wall composition" class="col-span-1 w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <div class="col-span-2 flex flex-col gap-3">
