  <!-- CHAPTER 4,  THE WALL -->

  <section id="le-mur" class="py-24 lg:py-32 bg-[#E8E4DB]">
    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">
      <span class="block text-xs font-light tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#8B7A3A] mb-6">Chapter 4</span>
      <h2 class="font-playfair text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-medium text-[#2C2824] mb-12 tracking-tight leading-tight">
        The Wall
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Some walls aren't built from straw. The ones in the administration are among them.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        From the start we had a clear vision: an agritourism project with farming, tourism and residents. We knew where we wanted to go. But the local development plan didn't allow it. We needed a <strong>STECAL</strong>—a Secteur de Taille et de Capacité d'Accueil Limitées (limited size and capacity sector)—to authorize this change of use.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Meanwhile we worked with what the rules allowed. We started with the farm and obtained an agricultural permit. We built what we could build. And in parallel we worked iteratively on the STECAL—four permit versions, each adapted to the legal framework of the moment.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Four years. Four years of meetings, applications, letters, refusals, rewrites, waiting.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        One winter evening in 2022. Charly opens an envelope in the farm kitchen. Another refusal. The third time. Someone says, quietly: « Maybe we should stop. » Silence. The stove crackles. No one answers. No one stops.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-light text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The Grand Shambala build started in summer 2023, in parallel with the STECAL process that would conclude in summer 2025 with the new local plan. The building and the law moved forward together—not always at the same pace. The STECAL now allows the change of use toward the project's final vision.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="my-12 py-8 border-l-2 border-[#C4A855] pl-8">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light italic text-[#2C2824]/85 leading-relaxed">
          We always worked with what the rules allowed. And we always worked so the rules would catch up with the vision.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <img src="/images/laom/grand-shambala/permis-construire-chronologie-grand-shambala.webp" alt="Administrative documents and permit timeline, 4 years of process for Grand Shambala" title="Timeline of the 4-year administrative journey" class="w-full aspect-[16/9] object-cover rounded-sm" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </div>
  </section>


